It has been over a year since you last logged in to your Electroneum online=
 wallet (the Electroneum App or my.electroneum.com portal).

Because it's been a while and your balance is currently zero, we are closin=
g your wallet as part of our longer-term plan for the Electroneum app.

Why are we doing this?

Because Electroneum is now fully EVM compatible (as part of the Electroneum=
 2.0 launch) and being recognised as one of the fastest and lowest-cost sma=
rt contract blockchains available, it has been integrated by various third-=
party wallets with additional features.

Third-party wallets such as Zypto.com have integrated Electroneum (and even=
 offer a debit card) and have better features, allowing you to fully utilis=
e the Web3 opportunities that are now available to Electroneum users.

You can also add Electroneum to most EVM-compatible third-party wallets suc=
h as MetaMask, Trust Wallet, Coinbase Wallet (Base) and many more.

What's happening?

We are deactivating inactive wallets that don't have a balance as the first=
 stage of a longer-term plan to close the Electroneum app down.

There is a lot of overhead in maintaining the Electroneum App, and our team=
's focus is on rolling out new features and integrating Electroneum into mu=
ltiple corporate projects that we have ongoing.

What do you need to do?

You don't need to do a thing. We'll handle the closure on our end.

When you decide to revisit using Electroneum, simply integrate into one of =
the wallets mentioned above - or visit the Electroneum website for full det=
ails:

https://electroneum.com/

Keep an eye on our X channel for further information:

https://x.com/electroneum

All the best,
A Equipa Electroneum


